The paper describes an approach based on neural networks for predicting the destination of a taxi based on a variable-length sequence of GPS points and associated meta-information. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of recurrent neural networks and memory networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the use of GPS points suggests that the paper may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
